CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1941, pg. 10 reads: "Prizewinners At Show Featuring Latest In Hair Fashions - Mrs. E.P. Tunie, wife of the pastor of Clark Memorial Baptist church. Homestead in a hair style created by Jessie Weems of Homestead.  She was first prize winner in recent beauticians' show at Warren church...Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. E. P. Tunie, wife of Clark Memorial Baptist Church reverend, seated in profile modeling hairstyle, in Harris Studio
